Cols
data.description: Specifies which URL metrics to retrieve for a target URL.

data.name: Filter
data.description: Filter excludes results for Mozscape calls that do not meet specified criteria. For example, followed links and equity links often affect search engine results more than other types of links, so it's useful to filter for equity links or only some types of equity links.  The links, anchor-text, and top-pages endpoints each accept different Filter values.  For links calls, Filter is additive: you can apply more than one filter to a query. Use the "plus" symbol + between criteria to specify more than one filter parameter. Filter is a true logical "and", meaning results return only if they meet all filter criteria.  For anchor-text and top-pages calls, Mozscape accepts only one Filter value.

data.name: Limit
data.description: Specifies a maximum number of results to return for a call.  Limit ensures the results of an API call are easy for your application to handle and helps ensure timely API responses when you submit a query for a target URL with many potential source URLs. (Returning large amounts of data can cause Mozscape to time out.)  The default value for Limit is 25. The maximum value is 50.

data.name: LinkCols
data.description: Specifies which link metrics to retrieve for a link. Only links calls use this parameter.

data.name: Offset
data.description: Specifies a number of results to skip past.  Offset helps when making multiple Mozscape calls for information about the same URL or URLs. For example, to find all source URLs pointing to moz.com (a number in the thousands), make several calls with increasing Offset values until all results return.  The default value of Offset is 0. Offsets greater than 100,000 return an empty array. Offsets inclusive of a hundred-thousandth result return up to that result. (Mozscape offers a maximum of 100,000 results per URL.)

data.name: Scope
data.description: Scope narrows results by returning only certain kinds of links. For example, Scope can help you find all unique domains linking to a target URL you specify.  Use Scope for analyzing domain-level metrics. For example, a Mozscape call with Scope=domain_to_page&Limit=1&Sort=page_authority returns the unique domain with the highest page authority for the target URL. Only links and anchor-text calls accept Scope values. Each endpoint has its own set of possible values.

data.name: Sort
data.description: Sort orders results in descending order for a particular value. Only links, metadata, and top-pages endpoints accept Sort parameters.  Mozscape allows one Sort value per call. The default value of Sort is page_authority.

data.name: SourceCols
data.description: Specifies which URL metrics to retrieve for the source URL of a link. Only links calls use this parameter.

data.name: target_url
data.description: The URL for the link you want to analyze.

data.name: TargetCols
data.description: Specifies which URL metrics to retrieve for the target URL of a link. Only links calls use this parameter.

The url-metrics Mozscape endpoint returns metrics for a URL or set of URLs you specify. Use the Cols parameter to specify which metrics to return; enter the sum of the bit flag values for each metric.  For a single URL, use a GET requestthe typical Mozscape format, with all information contained in the body of a single URL. Use batched calls for more than one URL.  Response fields help you organize the information Mozscape returns.
data.name: url-metrics

description: The Mozscape API allows you to customize and integrate data from our dynamic Mozscape index right into your own applications. Our Mozscape index is updated frequently to ensure that you're getting the freshest look at the web possible. With billions of links in our index, intelligent metrics, and thorough URL data, our Mozscape API offers unlimited possibilities.
